# Cleaning Log

## Cleaning Philosophy

This project followed a data-integrity-first approach designed to preserve the reliability and traceability of the original dataset.

All validation activities were completed before any cleaning or transformation decisions were made.

The original dataset was preserved throughout the project, and all approved transformations were performed only within the Working_Data environment.

Guiding principles included:

* Preserve original source data
* Validate before modifying
* Document all cleaning decisions
* Avoid unsupported assumptions
* Maintain analytical transparency

---

# Data Validation Summary

Before cleaning activities began, the dataset was reviewed for:

* Dataset structure consistency
* Duplicate records
* Duplicate fields
* Missing values
* Placeholder values
* Formatting inconsistencies
* Numeric field validation
* Geographic field consistency

The validation process ensured that cleaning decisions were supported by available evidence and business context.

---

# Cleaning Activities Performed

## Brand Standardization

### Issue Identified

A brand value of:

```text
Rin.G
```

was identified during the formatting review.

### Validation Performed

The following fields were reviewed:

* Product Title
* Smart Home Ecosystem
* Product Context

### Findings

* Product titles referenced Ring products.
* Smart Home Ecosystem was classified as Ring (Amazon).
* No evidence suggested Rin.G represented a separate brand.

### Action Taken

Standardized:

```text
Rin.G → Ring
```

### Location

Working_Data only

### Result

Improved brand consistency while preserving the original source data.

---

## Product Type Standardization

### Issue Identified

Multiple naming variations were identified for the same product category.

### Original Values

* Bullet Or Dome
* Bullet/ Dome For Option!

### Standardized Value

```text
Bullet / Dome
```

### Validation

Product titles and category classifications confirmed all values represented the same product category.

### Action Taken

Standardized values within Working_Data.

