# Structural Validation Review

## Duplicate Field Assessment

Repeated field names were identified during dataset validation.

Examples included:

* Title
* Brand
* Product Type
* Primary Category
* Smart Home Ecosystem
* Brand Tier
* Condition
* Condition Score

### Validation Findings

Field comparisons revealed that some repeated columns contained identical values while others contained materially different information.

### Decision

No columns were removed during validation.

### Reason

The available dataset documentation did not provide sufficient evidence to justify structural modifications.

The original dataset structure was preserved until SQL preparation was completed.

---

# Placeholder Value Review

## Product Type Assessment

### Observation

A small number of records contained placeholder values.

### Validation Performed

Reviewed:

* Product Title
* Product Category
* Product Context

### Decision

No values were replaced.

### Reason

While probable classifications could be inferred, no documented business rules existed to support automated replacement.

Original values were retained to preserve data integrity.

